    "deal_descriptions": {
      "short_description": "Semiconductor equipment maker Yanwei Semiconductor raised a nearly \u00a5700 million Series A round from Hillhouse Capital, Shixi Capital, CICC Capital and a consortium of new and returning investors.",
      "long_description": "Yanwei Semiconductor closed a Series A financing of almost RMB 700 million. New investors included Shixi Capital, Goldstone Investment, Hillhouse Capital, Anxin Capital, Fengyuan Capital, Xincheng Capital, CICC Capital, TEDA Kechuang Investment, Jinyuan Capital, Hefei Industrial Investment, Dianshi Capital and Yongxin Ark. Existing shareholders Hushan Capital, Xianghe Capital, Yida Capital, Xinke Capital and Primavera Capital also participated, increasing their stakes. The capital mix was entirely equity according to the disclosure. Proceeds will support core product upgrades, capacity build-out and R&D expansion to accelerate domestic replacement of high-end thin-film deposition tools. The company, located in Jiangsu, did not reveal earlier round sizes but noted several prior backers in this raise. No additional financial metrics or valuation figures were provided beyond the \u201cnear RMB 700 million\u201d headline amount."
    },
