    "deal_descriptions": {
      "short_description": "Brazilian fintech 99Pay raised R$ 700 million (\u2248 US$135 million) through a FIDC vehicle coordinated and co-invested by Bradesco BBI, with 99 also participating.",
      "long_description": "99 completed a R$ 700 million (\u2248 US$135 million) fundraising via a Fundo de Investimento em Direitos Credit\u00f3rios (FIDC), its third such structure since it began lending in November 2022. The FIDC was exclusively coordinated by Bradesco BBI, which also invested alongside the company itself. Proceeds will be used to expand 99Pay\u2019s credit offering to its user base. Cumulatively, 99Pay has originated around R$ 6 billion in loans and holds an active portfolio of roughly R$ 1.8 billion. No additional external investors or equity components were disclosed in the article. The transaction reinforces 99\u2019s strategy of using structured credit vehicles to finance loan growth within Brazil\u2019s regulated fintech sector."
    },
